# Cartographic Concept #2

### Cartographic Generalization

#### abstract spatial information at a high level of detail to information that can be rendered on a map at a lower level of detail.
.center[<img src="img/generalization.png" width= 70%/>]
.footnote[[source](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cartographic_generalization)]

---

background-size: cover
class: left ,top
# Cartographic Concept #3

### Map Insets

#### An inset map is a smaller map inset within a larger map. ... Inset maps can show the location of the main map in the context of a larger area. 
<br>
.center[<img src="img/inset.1.png" width= 80%/>]
.footnote[[source](https://www.cnn.com/)]

---


